quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  9,75,"And of them are the ones who covenanted with Allah, \"If He bring us of His Grace, indeed we will definitely donate (i.e., give alms) and indeed we will definitely be of the righteous"
  9,76,"Yet, as soon as He brought them of His Grace, they were miserly with it and turned back (while) they are veering away (from His Words)"
  9,77,So He has made the consequence (to be) hypocrisy in their hearts until the Day they meet Him for that they failed Allah in what they promised Him and for that they were often lying
  9,78,Do they not know that Allah knows their secret and their private conference and that Allah is The Sublime Knower of the things Unseen
  9,79,"The ones who defame the ones of the believers who volunteer (their) donations and the ones who find (nothing) except their endeavor, and so scoff at them; (i.e., they scoff at the believers who volunteer their donations, as well as the believers who do not donate) Allah has scoffed at them; and they will have a painful torment"
  9,80,"Ask forgiveness for them, or do not ask forgiveness for them; in case you ask forgiveness for them seventy times, yet Allah will never forgive them; that (is) for that they disbelieved in Allah and His Messenger; and Allah does not guide the immoral people"
  9,81,"The ones who were left behind exulted with their seat (s) behind the back of Messenger of Allah, (i.e., against the wishes of the Messenger) and hated to strive with their riches and their selves in the way of Allah, and said, \"Do not march out in the heat.\" Say, \"The fire of Hell is strictly hotter, \" if they (really) comprehend"
  9,82,"So, let them laugh a little and weep much in recompense for what they have been earning"
  9,83,"Then, in case Allah returns you to a section of them, (and) so they ask permission of you to go out, then say, \"You shall never go out with me at all, and you shall never fight with me any enemy; surely you were satisfied with sitting back the first time, so sit back with the ones who tarry behind"
  9,84,"And do not pray at all over any of them (when) he is dead, nor rise up over (i.e., stand over) his tomb; surely they disbelieve in Allah and His Messenger and died while they were immoral"
  9,85,"And do not let their riches and children make you admire them. Surely Allah only wills thereby to torment them in the present (life), and that their selves expire while they are disbelievers"
  9,86,"And when a s?rah is sent down (saying), \"Believe in Allah and strive with His Messenger, \" those endowed with ampleness among them ask you permission (i.e., permission to stay behind and not fight) and say, \"Leave us (behind) with the ones sitting back"
  9,87,"They are satisfied to be with the ones tarrying behind, (i.e. among the women, who generally remain behind) and their hearts are stamped upon, so they do not comprehend"
  9,88,But the Messenger and the ones who have believed with him have striven with their riches and their selves; and those will have the most charitable (benefits) and those are they (who) are prosperous
  9,89,"Allah has prepared for them Gardens from beneath which the Rivers run, eternally (abiding) therein; that is the magnificent triumph"
  9,90,And (some) Arabs (of the desert) came with ready excuses that they might be permitted (not to go out); and the ones who lied to Allah and His Messenger sat back (at home). There will afflict the ones of them who have disbelieved a painful torment
  9,91,"There is no restriction for the weak nor for the sick nor for the ones who do not find (anything) to expend, when they give (honest) advice to Allah and His Messenger. In no way is there any (restriction) against the fair-doers; and Allah is Ever-Forgiving, Ever-Merciful"
  9,92,"Nor (is there any restriction) against the ones who, when they came up to you for you to transport them, you said, \"I do not find that which to transport you, \" they turned away, and their eyes overflowing with tears, grieved that they did not find (anything) to expend"